                "title": "The Great Family Reunion of 2015",
                "content": {
                    "type": "doc",
                    "content": [
                        {
                            "type": "heading",
                            "attrs": {
                                "level": 1
                            },
                            "content": [
                                {
                                    "text": "The Great Family Reunion of 2015",
                                    "type": "text"
                                }
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "paragraph",
                            "content": [
                                {
                                    "text": "It was William who first suggested we organize a proper family reunion. The last time the entire Smith clan had gathered was at Grandpa James' funeral in 2005, and we all agreed it was time for happier memories.",
                                    "type": "text"
                                }
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "paragraph",
                            "content": [
                                {
                                    "text": "We chose July 4th weekend at the old family ranch in Houston. Over 50 family members attended, spanning four generations. Jennifer set up her easel and painted portraits of the great-grandchildren. Michael led a morning 5K run that even some of the grandkids completed.",
                                    "type": "text"
                                }
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "paragraph",
                            "content": [
                                {
                                    "text": "The highlight was William's presentation of the family tree he'd been researching. Using old photos and documents, he traced our lineage back to Ireland and showed us connections we never knew existed. It sparked hours of storytelling as the elders shared memories of people we'd only heard whispers about.",
                                    "type": "text"
                                }
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "paragraph",
                            "content": [
                                {
                                    "text": "We decided that day to make it an annual tradition.",
                                    "type": "text",
                                    "marks": [
                                        {
                                            "type": "bold"
                                        }
                                    ]
                                }
                            ]
                        }

            "details": {
                "id": "c613f172-aece-488d-9a0a-4027e6f602a9",
                "title": "Grandpa James' War Stories",
                "content": {
                    "type": "doc",
                    "content": [
                        {
                            "type": "heading",
                            "attrs": {
                                "level": 1
                            },
                            "content": [
                                {
                                    "text": "Grandpa James' War Stories",
                                    "type": "text"
                                }
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "paragraph",
                            "content": [
                                {
                                    "text": "James rarely talked about the war. But on his 80th birthday, surrounded by family, he finally opened up about his experiences in the Pacific.",
                                    "type": "text"
                                }
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "heading",
                            "attrs": {
                                "level": 2
                            },
                            "content": [
                                {
                                    "text": "The Bronze Star",
                                    "type": "text"
                                }
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "paragraph",
                            "content": [
                                {
                                    "text": "He earned the Bronze Star in the Philippines in August 1945. His unit was pinned down by enemy fire, and despite being wounded, he carried three injured soldiers to safety. He never saw it as heroism - just doing what anyone would do for their brothers in arms.",
                                    "type": "text"
                                }
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "paragraph",
                            "content": [
                                {
                                    "text": "After the war, he kept in touch with those three men until they passed away. Every Veterans Day, he would write letters to their families.",
                                    "type": "text"
                                }
                            ]
                        }
                    ]
                },
                "tree_id": "bda0fb4f-ef12-403f-8dc4-dd103066285a",

            "details": {
                "id": "fe96eed1-bb11-4725-aa05-73d821dc98cf",
                "title": "The Williams Family Journey from Ireland",
                "content": {
                    "type": "doc",
                    "content": [
                        {
                            "type": "heading",
                            "attrs": {
                                "level": 1
                            },
                            "content": [
                                {
                                    "text": "From Dublin to Chicago: The Williams Story",
                                    "type": "text"
                                }
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "paragraph",
                            "content": [
                                {
                                    "text": "Robert Williams arrived at Ellis Island in 1910 at age 8, clutching his mother's hand and a small suitcase containing everything they owned.",
                                    "type": "text"
                                }
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "paragraph",
                            "content": [
                                {
                                    "text": "His father had come to America a year earlier to work in the steel mills of Chicago, saving enough money to bring the rest of the family over. Robert never forgot his first sight of the Statue of Liberty or the overwhelming chaos of Ellis Island.",
                                    "type": "text"
                                }
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "paragraph",
                            "content": [
                                {
                                    "text": "He grew up in Chicago's Irish community, started working at the steel mill at 16, and became a passionate advocate for workers' rights. He helped organize one of the first successful union drives at his plant in 1935.",
                                    "type": "text"
                                }
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "paragraph",
                            "content": [
                                {
                                    "text": "His famous words:",
                                    "type": "text",
                                    "marks": [
                                        {
                                            "type": "italic"
                                        }
                                    ]
                                }
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "paragraph",
                            "content": [
                                {
                                    "text": "‚ÄúWe came here with nothing but hope. Now we fight to ensure others have the same chance we did.‚Äù",
                                    "type": "text",
                                    "marks": [
                                        {
                                            "type": "bold"
                                        }
                                    ]
                                }
                            ]
                        }
                    ]
                },

        {
            "details": {
                "id": "a5c2ed6d-f63b-4c3d-b152-d27cb46cf34d",
                "title": "The Great County Fair Pie Contest of 1955",
                "content": {
                    "type": "doc",
                    "content": [
                        {
                            "type": "heading",
                            "attrs": {
                                "level": 1
                            },
                            "content": [
                                {
                                    "text": "The Great County Fair Pie Contest of 1955",
                                    "type": "text"
                                }
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "paragraph",
                            "content": [
                                {
                                    "text": "It was a sweltering July day, but Mary was cool as a cucumber. She had been perfecting her apple pie recipe for months, using a secret blend of spices she swore she'd take to her grave.",
                                    "type": "text"
                                }
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "paragraph",
                            "content": [
                                {
                                    "text": "Her biggest rival, Mrs. Higgins, had won three years in a row. But this year, Mary had a secret weapon: apples from James's new orchard.",
                                    "type": "text"
                                }
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "paragraph",
                            "content": [
                                {
                                    "text": "When the judges took their first bite, silence fell over the tent. Then, a collective sigh of happiness. Mary didn't just win; she set a record score that still stands today.",
                                    "type": "text"
                                }
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "paragraph",
                            "content": [
                                {
                                    "text": "The Blue Ribbon still hangs in our kitchen.",
                                    "type": "text",
                                    "marks": [
                                        {
                                            "type": "bold"
                                        }
                                    ]
                                }
                            ]
                        }
                    ]
                },

        {
            "details": {
                "id": "09c67bae-f608-4df2-8c14-9c28caaa239d",
                "title": "The One That Didn't Get Away",
                "content": {
                    "type": "doc",
                    "content": [
                        {
                            "type": "heading",
                            "attrs": {
                                "level": 1
                            },
                            "content": [
                                {
                                    "text": "The One That Didn't Get Away",
                                    "type": "text"
                                }
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "paragraph",
                            "content": [
                                {
                                    "text": "John and William went fishing every summer at Lake George. Usually, they came back with nothing but mosquito bites and empty coolers.",
                                    "type": "text"
                                }
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "paragraph",
                            "content": [
                                {
                                    "text": "But in the summer of '85, something miraculous happened. William, only 15 at the time, hooked something massive. It took both of them 20 minutes to reel it in.",
                                    "type": "text"
                                }
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "paragraph",
                            "content": [
                                {
                                    "text": "It was a 12-pound bass! They were so excited they almost tipped the canoe over. They took a photo that ended up in the local newspaper under the headline 'Local Boy Catches Lake Monster'.",
                                    "type": "text"
                                }
                            ]
                        }
                    ]
